# CHALLENGE: Mutate Rename Circular Reference
# Validates how the parser handles sequential rename operations that form a circular reference.
# In Logstash/SecOps configs, `rename` operations in a single `mutate` block are processed
# in the order they are defined.
# The tool MUST trace the field lineage sequentially without falling into an infinite loop
# or raising a maximum recursion depth error during static analysis.
# EXPECTED BEHAVIOR: `field_a` -> `field_b`, `field_b` (old) -> `field_c`, `field_c` (old) -> `field_a`.
filter {
  mutate {
    rename => {
      "field_a" => "field_b"
      "field_b" => "field_c"
      "field_c" => "field_a"
    }
  }
}
